I can probably take this. It looks like there are a number of things we need to merge to main before regenerating the tickets?

It looks like the follow up to #8169 was merged as #8245. Do we need to merge #8088 and a CI-only version of #8193 before generating the images? It looks like #8268 failed a flaky test in the TF frontend, @areusch can you rebase? 

@Lunderberg Do you want to make a PR for the TF update?

@jwfromm And added meta-tests for all the new functionality.

@tmoreau89 Good point, that was an intentional choice to point to the main branch of tvm-rfcs.  I figured that since the main discussion was on the intended behavior, it would be likely that the two would be accepted or rejected together.

Thank you both for the reviews, and I think the only thing remaining is the CI.

@areusch is out this week, but his sphinx fix had a syntax error. If someone could review this, I'd appreciate it:
https://github.com/apache/tvm/pull/8316

With that PR and the other two linked above, I can build the ci_cpu, ci_gpu, and ci_arm images. ci_qemu is failing with a gpg error that arose with one of these PRs, I've asked @mehrdadh to debug. https://github.com/apache/tvm/pull/8156 https://github.com/apache/tvm/pull/8190
